oofem.out
2D unsaturated mass-transport on 100x100 mm rect with circular inclusions
nltransienttransportproblem nsteps 100 deltat 1.0 rtol 1.e-3 alpha 1. nsmax 200 nmodules 1
vtkxmllattice tstep_step 1 dofman_all primvars 1 6
domain 2dMassLatticeTransport
OutputManager tstep_all dofman_all
ncrosssect 0 nmat 2 nbc 1 nic 1 nltf 1 nset 1
# matrix: high permeability
latticetransmat 1 d 1.e3 k 1.e-12 vis 1.e-3 thetas 0.10 thetar 0. ctor 0.001
# aggregate: low permeability
latticetransmat 2 d 1.e3 k 1.e-18 vis 1.e-3 thetas 0.01 thetar 0. ctor 0.001
# Saturated bottom (y=ymin); the rest of the specimen starts dry via the
# initial condition below and saturates over time.
BoundaryCondition 1 loadTimeFunction 1 prescribedvalue 1.
InitialCondition 1 Conditions 1 u 0.0 dofs 1 11 set 1
ConstantFunction 1 f(t) 1.
Set 1 allelements
#@grid 2dTM
#@mesher qhull
#@diam 0.002
#@perflag 2 0 0
#@thickness 1.0
#@lumpedcapacity 1
#@rect 1 box 4 0. 0. 0.1 0.1
# Any element with at least one endpoint in an aggregate disk takes the
# low-permeability aggregate material (mat 2) — both `inside` (both ends
# in) and `interface` (one in, one out) route to mat 2. Edges with both
# endpoints in the matrix keep the default mat 1.
#@inclusionfile packing.dat itz 1.e-9 inside 2 interface 2
#@nodebc 1 face 2 min
